cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper presents a framework for learning to plan hierarchically in domains with unknown dynamics, which involves several aspects of artificial intelligence (AI) such as reinforcement learning, skill learning, and generalization. The paper also includes experiments on a robotic manipulator, indicating a focus on robotics (RO) and systems (SY). The use of curriculum learning suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and the paper proposes a new method for learning abstract skills, which could be relevant to programming languages (PL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.PL, in that order.
